keywords: 2 Item Crohn's Disease, Patient reported outcome, CD-PRO-2, PROM
en.use: This archetype represents a patient assessment that needs to be filled up everyday and when getting the total days necessary to do the calculation for the total scores, a final composition submission must be present. This means that in order to achieve the total score, multi submissions must be sent to the database and in order to achieve this the composition should have different versions during his lifecycle. This archetype includes several single point events which include the total scores for each abdominal pain and number of stools. In the 7 days point events these elements should be constrained to 0 at the template level or in the run time, being only filled in on the interval events for 7 days average and total score where the count and ordinals for number of stools and abdominal pain should be constrained to 0.

en.purpose: Assess the size of mucosal ulcers, the ulcerated surface, the endoscopic extension and the presence of stenosis and give a score for interpretation of the stage of the disease.
